lead_paragraph: Jubilant Chicago Cubs fans spilled from sports bars, restaurants and viewing parties across the city to celebrate their beloved team's first World Series triumph in 108 years on Wednesday.

headline.print_headline: Wrigleyville Goes Bonkers as Cubs End 108-Year Drought
